Show HN: I made a minimalist time blocking app 2.0
text:
I made a time blocking app with a minimalist look & feel, only time blocking one day at a time, customisable intervals and easy to organize without overlapping with new updates: - new minimalist design - set colour to your time blocks - smooth drag and drop to organize your time blocks

You can try it for free at https://timeist.app/demo. Thanks for checking out Timeist 2.0. Feel free to leave any feedback or suggestions

Ask HN: What are great resources to catch up C++?
text:
I programmed C++ more than 10 years till around 2015. Most of my coding were using C++98, a little bit C++11. Now I am about to come back to C++ dev. I checked out some C++ code online, seems STD library has a lot more added, lamda is fairly popularly used (maybe recommended?), etc. Somehow the C++ code look to me quite foreign. Is there any great resource for people like me to re-connect with the latest C++?

I believe my OO understanding is still solid, just want to catch up.
